Source: hwsetup-kanotix
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>
Build-Depends: cdbs (>= 0.4.23-1.1), debhelper (>= 5.0.0), kudzu-kanotix-dev
Standards-Version: 3.6.2

Package: hwsetup-kanotix
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, kudzu-kanotix (<< 1.2.0), kudzu-kanotix-vesa (<< 1.2.0), hwdata-kanotix (<< 0.169)
Description: Automatic hardware setup using the kudzu library
 hwsetup is a non-interactive hardware setup tool that tries to read your
 hardware setup and autoloads all necessary modules, plus generating the
 symlinks for mouse and cdrom/scanner in /dev.
